Where Are You From?

	1.	Formal Question:
	•	Woher kommen Sie?
	•	Woher = where from
	•	kommen = to come
	•	Sie = you (formal)
	2.	Informal Question:
	•	Woher kommst du?
	•	Woher = where from
	•	kommst = to come (2nd person singular, informal)
	•	du = you (informal)

Answering the Question:

	1.	Formal or Informal Answer:
	•	Ich komme aus Hyderabad. (I come from Hyderabad.)
	•	Ich = I
	•	komme = to come (1st person singular)
	•	aus = from
You can replace Hyderabad with the name of your city or country.
	2.	Shortened Response:
	•	Simply say Aus Hyderabad (From Hyderabad).

Extra Examples:

	1.	Where do you come from (plural/formal)?
	•	Woher kommen Sie alle? (Where do you all come from?)
	2.	Where does he/she come from?
	•	Woher kommt er? (Where does he come from?)
	•	Woher kommt sie? (Where does she come from?)
	3.	Additional Answers:
	•	Ich komme aus Deutschland. (I come from Germany.)
	•	Ich komme aus Indien. (I come from India.)

Summary:

	•	Formal: Woher kommen Sie?
	•	Informal: Woher kommst du?
	•	Answer: Ich komme aus [city/country].
